definition: background/bottom/base/end (of the month, year etc)/remnants/(math.) radix/base

sentences.english: Get simply very dinkum , calm very thoroughly.
sentences.chinese: 简单得很纯粹，平静得很彻底。

sentences.english: Satan and the rebel angels have been roundly defeated.
sentences.chinese: 撒旦和叛乱天使们被彻底击败了。

sentences.english: It was this journey that changed Jiang Hao’s life radically.
sentences.chinese: 正是这次美国之旅，彻底改变了姜浩的人生。

sentences.english: The utility model thoroughly solves the wind-proof problem and the slide-proof problem; heavy equipment can not be damaged by the utility model.
sentences.chinese: 彻底解决了防风抗滑问题，保住重大设备不受损失。

sentences.english: It would be a complete mistake to decry love of power altogether as a motive.
sentences.chinese: 反对对权力的迷恋是人们的动机之一是个彻底的错误。

sentences.english: The institute called the policy “a resounding success.
sentences.chinese: 卡托研究所称这个政策是“一场彻底的胜利。”

sentences.english: We have abolished the system of exploitation of man by man.
sentences.chinese: 我们已经彻底废除了人剥削人的制度。

sentences.english: The general anesthesia therapy dose are few, regains consciousness thoroughly, rapid, the controllability is good.
sentences.chinese: 全麻药用量少，苏醒彻底，迅速，可控性好。

sentences.english: Surrounded by guardsoul the little guy can perish the old guy thoroughly.
sentences.chinese: 被守护魄环绕着的小家伙能彻底毁灭老家伙。

sentences.english: Rinse ice bucket thoroughly after use.
sentences.chinese: 使用后要彻底洗净冰桶。

sentences.english: He was completely and entirely in the present.
sentences.chinese: 他完全彻底地活在当下。

sentences.english: The mild Mr. Tyson was completely foxed by his wife.
sentences.chinese: 温厚的泰森先生被他妻子彻底蒙骗了。

sentences.english: But some problems about the white bole efficient utilization have not been solved thoroughly.
sentences.chinese: 但对碱回收的白泥有效利用问题没能彻底的解决。

sentences.english: Despite a thorough investigation, on trace of Mary has been found.
sentences.chinese: 尽管查得很彻底，但还是找不到玛丽的一点踪迹。

sentences.english: If this problem can't be solved, the reforms of state-owned enterprises can't go well.
sentences.chinese: 这个问题解决不好，国企改革就会难以彻底。

sentences.english: Sometimes I'm afraid I'll just go to pieces .
sentences.chinese: 有时候我真担心我会彻底垮下来。

definition: (completed action marker)/(modal particle indicating change of state, situation now)/(modal particle intensifying preceding clause)
to finish/to achieve/variant of 瞭|了[liao3]/to understand clearly
to yield/to permit/to let sb do sth/to have sb do sth/to make sb (feel sad etc)/by (indicates the agent in a passive clause, like 被[bei4])
of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)
